<br>
Most Seahorses are clerics and CH themselves or their comrades when they get below 50%.  Other than that they have low hp but high Aggro (except the Swirlspines in Phin's of course, they have high hp).  So obviously you're not going to be able to interrupt their CH and thats really what makes them so tough to solo.  The best thing to do is to pull them with another creature.  Its best to nab a seahorse (or the two if you're camping Temple of Prexus) and also nab one of those pirahnas in the ceiling (they can be single pulled, if you're high enough level).  Use Dizil's Deafening Decoy or Epic pet for this, since you'll want to keep aggro on pet and it needs to take alot of punishment.  Pull the mobs to the camping spot to the left of the entrance.  <br>
<br>
Put the pet on the pirhana and nuke it to half (takes 1 Char or 2 Scars of Sigil w/ Focus items).  The Seahorses both will heal it.  Repeat again.  Seahorses CH again.  Again.  Seahorses may CH again if they have the mana.  By this time the Seahorses are out of mana and can't CH, take out the Pirahana with a couple of more nukes (also probably wasting the seahorsies mana for lesser heal) and open your spell book to grab your best pet (any is good, except fire of course).  Be ready to chain cast it when Dizil's Decoy goes down (this is how I do  it because I don't have epic pet yet, epic pet could probably take the damage and still keep kickin).  Use that pet and remaining mana to take down the cleric seahorses at will (takes about 3 nukes w/ pet hitting to kill).  Once you have them both dead be absolutley ready for respawn in the Temple (not sure on time), so you can nab the Seahorse as soon as it spawns and seperate it from its counter part.  i've never attempted the one in the ceiling and honestly he usually doesn't come.  Not sure how well you'd do against him.  He's a swirlspine is he not?<br>
<br>
The biggest problem with this is that there is a roaming seahorse that will come over and start healing your seahorsies even after you've drained them on mana.  You'll want to wait for that seahorse to come around and then pull as soon as he leaves the room to time it right.  Once you're done with the two horses in Prexus temple you should have enough mana to pull the roamer after a bit of medding.  Remember to grab a pirahna along with him so you can drain his CH power.  <br>
<br>
Thats my advice.  Did it once when I was bored.  I'm sure we're all sick of Kedge by now.<br>
<br>
The same strategy can be applied to Seahorses in Phin's lair btw.  Most people camp out when they get multiple swirlspines (because they can't be mezzed and they CH each  other), but really between their casting and their not so fast attack rate, one group could take 4 swirlspines at one time.  Focus all attack power on one (maybe put a Pet, Dizil's works well here too, on a couple of them.  Note the danger of the shimmering sailfins and account for it by keeping your pet away from them).  When that one gets down in health (below half) all 4 of the seahorses will CH, wasting all their mana.  Bring it down to half again, same thing.  Since it takes a bit of time to get swirlspines down in health and they are normally casting during the intermediate periods, it usually takes 2 CHs for a Swirlspine to run out of mana.  Once the first Seahorse is taken care of, taking the other 3 is just like killing 3 warrior mobs with less hp and less attack.  <br>
<br>
With low hp and low attack mobs that CH, the best thing to do is to bring them in packs and let them waste mana on each other.  So far the strategy has worked fairly well, but it takes a lot of practice to master.<br>
<br>
-Esmos Darkmage <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/unanamarinfernostorm.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Nanamar Infernostorm</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Arch Mage</span><br>  Posts: 390<br> <font color=#333333>(5/13/02 4:11:27 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm24.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=172.topic&index=16>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Solo'ing in Kedge ?</span><hr size=1> Um... y not just seeking flames while its CHing, should take it right out... or seeking flames followed right w/ scars when you see it nearing 1/2 hps... <p><body text=50/100/10> 
