<br>
Both types of seahorses are swirlspines, so people get confused.<br>
<br>
Four swirlspine seahorses spawn up at the top of Phinny's hole and I've never seen one mezzed or been able to personally land a debuff on one.  However, my fire nukes eat them up.<br>
<br>
Swirlspine guardians spawn down in the hole with Phinny.  I believe there are a max of two that can spawn there, and they spawn as you kill the swirlspine seahorses up top.  I can debuff them easily and have seen them charmed by a 56th level druid and mezzed by a 54th level chanter, even without my debuffs (not implying these are level limits, just saying that I've personally seen it). <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/ukinelaria.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Kinelaria</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Master Summoner</span><br>  Posts: 246<br> <font color=#333333>(6/4/02 2:33:34 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm24.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=172.topic&index=24>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Soloing in Kedge ?</span><hr size=1> Each of the 4 swirlspine seahorses has a chance at spawning a swirlspine guardian down in the pit with Phinny. Generally we always seem to get at least 2 guardians spawned clearing the swirlspines (pulling Phinny without them adding in isn't really feasible, possible maybe, but I've yet to see it done successfully).<br>
